name: Juggernaut Canyon
description:
Introduction

First Descent of a very cool canyon with a big rappel - 400' in a very rugged setting

Approach

Descent

The big 400' rappel can be broken into a two-stage descent by setting the 2nd lower rappel station in a hanging pothole along the way down - so you don't need a long rope for this canyon - should have a 300' rope though

Exit

Red tape

Beta sites

Trip reports and media

Background

First Descent of this canyon completed by Scott Swaney, Daniel Elson, and team (see report above) 4-2-16
